cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with relation extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the scope of cs.CL. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of neural networks and attention mechanisms in this paper falls under the scope of cs.AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The use of machine learning techniques such as neural networks and attention mechanisms in this paper falls under the scope of cs.LG. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - Relation extraction is also relevant to information retrieval, as it involves identifying and extracting relevant information from text. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The use of neural networks in this paper falls under the scope of cs.NE.
